  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "# Fine-Tuning Gemma 3 1B for Sherlock Holmes QA\n\nThis notebook fine-tunes `google/gemma-3-1b-it` on the Sherlock Holmes QA dataset (built in notebook 02) using **LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation)** via the Hugging Face TRL library.\n\n### Why LoRA?\nFine-tuning all 1 billion parameters of Gemma on a consumer GPU would require ~16 GB of VRAM and take many hours. LoRA sidesteps this by freezing the original model weights and injecting tiny trainable matrices (the \"adapters\") into the attention and MLP layers. Only the adapter parameters are updated \u2014 a fraction of the total \u2014 so training is fast and memory-efficient.\n\n### What this notebook does\n1. Loads the base model and the QA dataset.\n2. Replaces the generic system prompt with a Sherlock-specific one.\n3. Filters out low-quality examples.\n4. Trains with LoRA for 2 epochs.\n5. Merges the adapter into the base model and pushes the result to the Hub.\n\nThe merged model is then evaluated in notebook 04."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
