  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Configuration\n\nAll tunable parameters live in the `Config` class. Centralising them here means you only need to edit one place to switch model sizes, adjust sequence lengths, or change the output directory name."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "MqjLdOThRIte"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "# Define configuration parameters for the model and training run\nclass Config:\n    \"\"\"Configuration parameters \u2013 change values here rather than hunting through the code.\"\"\"\n\n    SIZE = \"3-1b\"                            # model size; alternatives: \"3-4b\", \"3-12b\"\n    MODEL_NAME = f\"google/gemma-{SIZE}-it\"   # base model to fine-tune\n    OUTPUT_MODEL = f\"gemma-{SIZE}-sherlock-expert\"  # local save directory name\n\n    max_seq_length = 2048  # maximum tokens per training example (longer sequences are truncated)\n    seed = 0               # random seed for full reproducibility"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Helper Functions\n\nThese utility functions handle environment setup (`init`), device selection (`info_device`), precision detection (`is_bfloat16_supported`), memory cleanup (`cleanup`), and reproducibility (`set_deterministic`).\n\nThe `set_deterministic` function is particularly important for fine-tuning experiments: setting all random seeds before training means that two runs with identical code and data will produce identical model weights, making results fully reproducible."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Ar0-cOqPRIlN"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "# \u2500\u2500 Environment and utility helpers \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n\ndef init():\n    \"\"\"Sets environment variables, logs in to Hugging Face, and clears GPU memory.\"\"\"\n    os.environ[\"TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM\"] = \"false\"  # avoid deadlocks in forked tokenizer processes\n    os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"0\"        # pin to the first GPU\n\n    token = os.environ.get(\"HF_TOKEN\")\n    if token:\n        login(token=token)\n    else:\n      try:\n        from google.colab import userdata\n        # Read the token stored in Colab's Secrets tab (\ud83d\udd11 icon)\n        hf_token = userdata.get('HF_TOKEN')\n        if hf_token:\n            login(token=hf_token, add_to_git_credential=True)\n            print(\"Hugging Face login successful using Google Colab secrets!\")\n        else:\n            print(\"Error: HF_TOKEN not found in Google Colab secrets or is empty.\")\n            print(\"Please ensure you have created a secret named 'HF_TOKEN' in the 'Secrets' tab (\ud83d\udd11) on the left sidebar.\")\n      except:\n        print(\"HF_TOKEN not set. You might need to log in manually.\")\n\n    torch.cuda.empty_cache()         # release any stale GPU allocations from a previous run\n    gc.collect()\n    warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n\ndef is_bfloat16_supported():\n    \"\"\"Returns True if the GPU supports bfloat16 (Ampere / RTX 30xx or newer).\"\"\"\n    if torch.cuda.is_available():\n        compute_dtype = torch.bfloat16 if torch.cuda.get_device_capability()[0] >= 8 else torch.float16\n    else:\n        compute_dtype = torch.bfloat16   # MPS (Apple Silicon) and modern CPUs handle bf16\n    return compute_dtype\n\ndef info_device():\n    \"\"\"Selects and returns the best available torch.device (CUDA > MPS > CPU).\"\"\"\n    
if torch.cuda.is_available():\n        device = torch.device(\"cuda\")\n    elif torch.backends.mps.is_available():\n        device = torch.device(\"mps\")\n    else:\n        device = torch.device(\"cpu\")\n    print(f"Using device: {device}")\n    return device\n\n\ndef cleanup(objects=None):\n    \"\"\"Deletes objects and flushes GPU memory.\"\"\"\n    if objects is not None:\n        for obj in objects:\n            del obj\n    torch.cuda.empty_cache()\n    gc.collect()\n\ndef set_deterministic(seed):\n    \"\"\"Sets all random seeds and CUDA settings for fully reproducible results.\"\"\"\n    random.seed(seed)\n    np.random.seed(seed)\n    torch.manual_seed(seed)\n    torch.cuda.manual_seed_all(seed)  # covers multi-GPU setups\n    set_seed(seed)                    # HF Transformers seed (covers sampling in generate)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "### Initialise the Environment"
