   ],
   "source": "# Initialise the environment, instantiate Config, select compute device,\n# and choose the optimal floating-point precision for this hardware.\ninit()\nparams = Config()\ndevice = info_device()\n# bfloat16 is preferred on Ampere+ GPUs; float16 is the safe fallback\ndtype = torch.bfloat16 if is_bfloat16_supported() else torch.float16\nprint(f\"Using dtype: {dtype}\")\nset_deterministic(params.seed)"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Dataset Loading\n\nWe wrap `load_dataset` in a `@retry` decorator from the `tenacity` library. This is a defensive measure: Hugging Face Hub downloads can occasionally fail with transient network errors, and without retry logic, a single blip would kill the entire training run."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "GsqZ-Jr3R12y"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "from tenacity import retry, stop_after_attempt, wait_fixed\n\n# @retry wraps get_data so that if the Hugging Face Hub returns a transient\n# error (e.g. a network blip or a 503), the function will automatically retry\n# up to 5 times, waiting 10 seconds between each attempt.\n@retry(stop=stop_after_attempt(5), wait=wait_fixed(10))\ndef get_data(repo_id, mapping_func=None, split=\"train\"):\n    \"\"\"Downloads a dataset split from Hugging Face Hub with automatic retries.\n\n    Args:\n        repo_id:      Hugging Face dataset identifier, e.g. 'lmassaron/Sherlock_QA'.\n        mapping_func: Optional callable applied row-by-row via Dataset.map().\n        split:        Which split to return ('train', 'test', 'validation', ...).\n    \"\"\"\n    print(f\"Attempting to load dataset {repo_id}, split {split}...\")\n    data = load_dataset(repo_id, cache_dir=\"/tmp\")[split]  # cache to /tmp to avoid filling home dir\n    if mapping_func:\n        data = data.map(mapping_func)\n    print(\"Dataset loaded successfully!\")\n    return data"
  },
