   "source": "# Start the training process.\n# TRL's SFTTrainer handles the training loop, periodic evaluation,\n# gradient accumulation, mixed-precision scaling, and checkpoint saving.\ntrainer.train()\n\n# Save the LoRA adapter weights locally as a checkpoint\ntrainer.model.save_pretrained(\"trained-model\")"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Visualising Training Progress\n\nPlot the training and validation loss curves. A healthy training run shows both curves decreasing together. If the validation loss starts rising while training loss keeps falling, the model is overfitting and training should be stopped earlier."
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
     "height": 472
    },
    "id": "3WzbnhgSXIVG",
    "outputId": "f0244f61-1b53-46b1-b752-79bdaa2b2b3d"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": "# \u2500\u2500 Plot training and validation loss curves \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n# The trainer records a log entry at every logging_steps interval.\n# Entries with a 'loss' key are training-step logs;\n# entries with 'eval_loss' are evaluation logs.\nlog_history = trainer.state.log_history\n\n# Extract training loss and the corresponding epoch numbers\ntrain_losses = [log[\"loss\"]       for log in log_history if \"loss\"       in log]\nepoch_train  = [log[\"epoch\"]      for log in log_history if \"loss\"       in log]\n\n# Extract validation loss and the corresponding epoch numbers\neval_losses  = [log[\"eval_loss\"]  for log in log_history if \"eval_loss\"  in log]\nepoch_eval   = [log[\"epoch\"]      for log in log_history if \"eval_loss\"  in log]\n\n# Plot both curves on the same axes\nplt.plot(epoch_train, train_losses, label=\"Training Loss\")\nplt.plot(epoch_eval,  eval_losses,  label=\"Validation Loss\")\nplt.xlabel(\"Epoch\")\nplt.ylabel(\"Loss\")\nplt.title(\"Training and Validation Loss per Epoch\")\nplt.legend()\nplt.grid(True)\nplt.show()"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
