   "source": "# Save the LoRA adapter weights and the tokeniser to a named directory,\n# then push both to the Hugging Face Hub.\n# The LoRA adapter is very small (a few MB) because only the low-rank\n# matrices are saved, not the full base model weights.\nif not DEMO:\n  lora_output_dir = f\"{params.OUTPUT_MODEL}-lora\"\n  trainer.model.save_pretrained(lora_output_dir)\n  print(f\"LoRA adapters saved to {lora_output_dir}\")\n  # Save the tokeniser alongside the adapter so inference code has everything it needs\n  tokenizer.save_pretrained(lora_output_dir)\n\n  repo_name = \"lmassaron/\" + lora_output_dir\n\n  # Push the LoRA adapter (NOT the full model) to the Hub\n  model.push_to_hub(repo_name)\n  tokenizer.push_to_hub(repo_name)\n\n  print(f\"Model and tokenizer pushed to {repo_name}\")"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": "## Merging and Uploading the Full Model\n\n`merge_and_unload()` mathematically combines the LoRA adapter with the base weights to produce a **single standalone model**. This merged model:\n- Loads like any standard `AutoModelForCausalLM` \u2014 no PEFT library needed.\n- Is the version loaded by notebook 04 for evaluation.\n- Is larger on disk (~2 GB) than the adapter alone (~50 MB), but is simpler to deploy."
